results.name: Number of primes between n^K and (n+1)^K, where K is 1.647862393566467... and n is an integer greater than 0.
comment: K is the smallest number such that there is always at least one prime between n^K and (n+1)^K for any integer n>0.
This is not the smallest K. See A143898. [From _T. D. Noe_, Sep 04 2008]
results.author: _Dmitry Kamenetsky_, Jan 11 2008
